 the material on this website should be sent us by <a href=\"mailto:mail@hoopassociates.co.uk\">email</a> or by letter to Hoop Associates, 34-35 Great Sutton Street, London EC1V 0DX.</p>\n<h2>Hyperlinking</h2>\n<p>You do not have to ask permission to link directly to the web pages hosted on this website. However, Hoop Associates does not permit its pages to be loaded into frames on your website as Hoop Associates pages must load into the user&#39;s entire window.</p>\n<p>Hoop Associates is not responsible for the content or reliability of any linked websites. Linking should not be taken as endorsement of any kind of the website linked to, including any products and services referred to in that website, nor does it imply that there is an association between Hoop Associates and the operators of that website. Hoop Associates cannot guarantee that these links will work all of the time and has no control over the availability of linked pages.</p>\n<h2>Cookies</h2>\n<p>Hoop may use \"cookies\" in order to personalise delivery of content based on your experience with our website.</p>\n<p>When you take part in the Hoop website, we may assign your computer browser a unique random number called a \"cookie\". We may also use flash cookies, which are managed as browser add-ons. Cookies enhance our website by allowing you faster access to the information you are seeking and by enabling us to provide suitable offers based on your experience with our site and products.</p>\n<p>Your privacy and security are not compromised when you accept a cookie from our website. A cookie simply contains a large random number which in itself does not contain any personal information and any information you submit in the registration section of the website will not be contained within the cookie data.</p>\n<p>Cookies from our server cannot read data from your computer&#39;s hard disc or read cookie files from other websites or write any information to your hard disc. They simply make the website easier for you to use.</p>\n<p>The use of cookies is an industry standard, and many major web sites use them to provide useful features for their customers. Each web site can send its own cookie to your browser if your browser&#39;s preferences allow it, but (to protect your privacy) your browser only permits a web site to access the cookies it has already sent to you, not the cookies sent to you by other sites.</p>\n<p>You can configure your browser to accept all cookies, reject all cookies, or notify you when a cookie is set. (Each browser is different, so check the \"Help\" menu of your browser to learn how to change your cookie preferences.)</p>\n<p>Flash cookies can be disabled or the data held deleted by changing your browser add-on settings or by visiting the website of the add-on manufacturer. If you reject all cookies, you may not be able to receive personalised information on our website.</p>\n<h2>Personal information</h2>\n<p>We will keep your information confidential except where disclosure is required or permitted by law (for example to government bodies and law enforcement agencies). Generally, we will only use your information within Hoop. However, sometimes Hoop uses third parties to process your information. Hoop requires these third parties to comply strictly with its instructions and Hoop requires that they do not use your personal information for their own business purposes, unless you have explicitly consented to the use of your personal information in this way.</p>\n<p>Your email address is used to only send you information that you have requested. Hoop adheres strictly to permission-based email policy. Hoop will not send you unsolicited email information, commercial offers or advertisements. Hoop will not sell, rent, or loan our contact lists or our customer&#39;s contact lists (including customer data) to any outside firms. All emails that you have requested will have an option to unsubscribe. Unsubscribe requests are fulfilled within minutes 